        dc:description           "FIG. 5. — Cheliferidae indet., tritonymph (ARC 186.1R): A, left chelicera, antiaxial face, spinneret broken; B, habitus, oblique dorsal view, some parts obscured, particularly palp and tergites on right side; right chela strongly foreshortened, only a few teeth shown (others not visible),granulation only partly indicated.Abbreviations:b, es, is, gs, ls, sb, setae of chelicera; eb, ib, isb, it, trichobothria of chela. Scale bar: A, 0.18 mm; B, 0.5 mm." ;
